DURBAN - Ten people were injured in two separate taxi accidents on Monday morning. Around 6am Rescue Care Paramedics attended to a taxi and car collision on the corner of Berea Road and Hunt Road. Five passengers had sustained minor injuries and were stabilised at the scene, before being transported to various Durban hospitals. Then before 7am, paramedics responded to another collision at the corner of Umbilo Road and Francois Road. When they arrived, they found that a taxi and car had collided at the junction, but the vehicles were spread apart because of the collision. Paramedics found that four passengers from the taxi had been injured as well as the driver of the car. They were stabilised on scene before being taken to hospitals. The cause of the collisions was unknown, however, police were on scene and were investigating. Daily News